# Nano ESP32 — WS2812B LED strip firmware

## Project context

This is a PlatformIO project targeting the Arduino Nano ESP32 (ESP32-S3 core, 3.3V logic).

### Hardware setup
- Board: Arduino Nano ESP32 (arduino_nano_esp32)
- Framework: Arduino
- LED library: FastLED
- 24x WS2812B LEDs, GRB order, 5V
- Powered via USB-C → VBUS pin provides 5V to strip
- Data line: GPIO6 → 74AHCT125 level shifter (3.3V→5V) → 300Ω resistor → strip DIN
- Toggle switch: SPST on GPIO4, INPUT_PULLUP, pin2 to GND
- 1000µF capacitor across strip 5V/GND pads
- Shared GND across all components

### platformio.ini
```ini
[env:arduino_nano_esp32]
platform = pioarduino
board = arduino_nano_esp32
framework = arduino
lib_deps = fastled/FastLED
```

### Firmware logic
- Toggle switch advances a state machine on every edge transition (either direction)
- Cycle: off (black) → mode 1 → off (black) → mode 2 → repeat
- FastLED.setBrightness(128) — 50% cap to stay within USB VBUS current budget (~720mA)
- Debounce: 50ms

### Base firmware (src/main.cpp)
```cpp
#include <FastLED.h>
#define LED_PIN     6
#define SWITCH_PIN  4
#define NUM_LEDS    24
CRGB leds[NUM_LEDS];
const int states[] = {0, 1, 0, 2};
int stateIndex = 0;
bool lastSwitchState = LOW;
unsigned long lastDebounce = 0;
const int DEBOUNCE_MS = 50;

void setup() {
  FastLED.addLeds<WS2812B, LED_PIN, GRB>(leds, NUM_LEDS);
  FastLED.setBrightness(128);
  pinMode(SWITCH_PIN, INPUT_PULLUP);
}

void loop() {
  bool current = digitalRead(SWITCH_PIN);
  if (current != lastSwitchState && millis() - lastDebounce > DEBOUNCE_MS) {
    lastDebounce = millis();
    lastSwitchState = current;
    stateIndex = (stateIndex + 1) % 4;
  }
  switch (states[stateIndex]) {
    case 0: fill_solid(leds, NUM_LEDS, CRGB::Black); break;
    case 1: // mode 1
      fill_solid(leds, NUM_LEDS, CRGB::White); break;
    case 2: // mode 2
      fill_solid(leds, NUM_LEDS, CRGB::Blue); break;
  }
  FastLED.show();
}
```

## Coding rules

- Always use FastLED — never Adafruit NeoPixel
- Keep GRB colour order for WS2812B
- Never exceed FastLED.setBrightness(128) unless the user explicitly confirms they are using an external PSU instead of VBUS
- The ESP32-S3 GPIO outputs 3.3V logic — the 74AHCT125 handles level shifting, but avoid anything that bypasses it
- When adding animations that block loop(), use millis()-based non-blocking patterns instead of delay()
- Always provide the full src/main.cpp when making changes — no partial snippets
- Flag any change that increases peak current draw above ~700mA

## Wiring constraints to keep in mind
- VBUS is limited by the USB host (typically 500mA laptop, up to 2A wall adapter)
- Adding more LEDs beyond 24 requires calculating new current budget before recommending
- A logic level shifter is required on the data line — do not suggest removing it
